records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - Deliver Heroin - No contest plea.  
Count 2 - Deliver Heroin - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, deliver heroin.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years.   One (1) year initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision consecutive to 12 CF 182 and 13 CF 875.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Pay costs of action; 
2) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
6) Obtain GED;
Count 2 - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years consecutive to count 1 and 12 CF 182 and 13 CF 875.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Pay costs of action; 
2) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC
3) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;;
6) Obtain GED.  
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.   
Minutes.
